text: Ezzat El Alaily () (15 September 1934 â€“ 5 February 2021) was an Egyptian actor. He appeared in over 300 movies, TV series, and theatre plays. His career began in the 1960s. He was born in Cairo. His best known roles were in Cairo (1963), The Land (1970), Kuwait Connection (1973), Alexandria... Why? (1979), Al Qadisiyya (1981), People on the Top (1981) and War in the Land of Egypt (1991).
